From 9a0c794f7d0ff6111e26f472218f60edadc5e0d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Jul 2025 14:11:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Upstream:DP:wifi:mac80211: Increase Tx headroom reservation

Currently while sending assoc request, skb is allocated using
alloc_skb() function.If extra_tx_headroom is 0 then max tx headroom
reserved for skb will be equal to IEEE80211_TX_STATUS_HEADROOM which
is 16 bytes.This headroom is utilized to add rtap header if the frame
is passed to monitor interface.Max rtap length calculation in function
ieee80211_tx_radiotap_len() can reach upto 24 bytes.So in case of
assoc request this can trigger low headroom scenario if frame is
passed to monitor interface.To avoid this increase tx headroom
reservation to 24 bytes.

Patch-dependency : None

Signed-off-by: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 include/net/mac80211.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/net/mac80211.h b/include/net/mac80211.h
index d9becbc..02647ba 100644
--- a/include/net/mac80211.h
+++ b/include/net/mac80211.h
@@ -5533,7 +5533,7 @@ void ieee80211_rx_nss_notify_4addr(struct net_device *dev, u8* sta_addr);
  * The TX headroom reserved by mac80211 for its own tx_status functions.
  * This is enough for the radiotap header.
  */
-#define IEEE80211_TX_STATUS_HEADROOM	ALIGN(14, 4)
+#define IEEE80211_TX_STATUS_HEADROOM	ALIGN(24, 4)
 
 /**
  * ieee80211_sta_set_buffered - inform mac80211 about driver-buffered frames
-- 
2.34.1

